 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add unit tests for SQLite store, projection builder, adapters, attention journal, and incident lifecycle","description":"Add focused package-local unit tests for the runtime data path so the redesign's hardest logic is pinned down before end-to-end coverage is asked to catch it. This task exists because the projection builder, normalization adapters, cursor logic, and incident lifecycle rules contain complex edge behavior that deserves direct tests, not just broad integration runs.","design":"The tests should cover migrations and store APIs, retention decisions, projection recompute behavior, adapter normalization, source_health derivation, degraded-state propagation, watermark handling, replay or resync rules, idempotent retry behavior, request or outcome correlation, duplicate suppression and cooldown or resurfacing rules, operator attention-state persistence and transitions, incident fingerprinting, promotion thresholds, recurrence handling, resolution or reopen behavior, and stable ordering. They should be table-driven, deterministic, and log fixture IDs, request IDs, idempotency keys, cursor values, reason codes, fingerprints, source-health changes, operator-state markers, suppression markers, and assertion diffs with enough detail to root-cause failures quickly.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the store, projection, adapter, attention, and incident packages each have strong unit coverage for happy-path, boundary, degraded, retry-safe, attention-hygiene, and operator-control conditions, with logging that makes failures actionable instead of cryptic.","notes":"This is the main unit-test bead for the runtime heart of the redesign. Keep the tests close to the packages they validate.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:48.913481831Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:27.302502372Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","unit","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:38.282625699Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:56.355821642Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:57.537765156Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:08.459186502Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:09.033011747Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:38.068514875Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:09.613121691Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:18:03.942894036Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:46.902361361Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:07.828602722Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:12.081736815Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:10.202180633Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:10.475739970Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:48.913481831Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:07.905984736Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":340,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: unit coverage must include event-class matching, selector or filter evaluation, heartbeat-emission decisions, idle-versus-stuck logic, adaptive cadence behavior, and durable-versus-ephemeral publication boundaries with detailed logs.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:05Z"},{"id":347,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical-store follow-up: unit tests must cover replay reconstruction correctness, replay snapshot caching, retention pruning, source-gap handling, stable replay identities, and evidence-link preservation across projection recompute paths.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:14Z"},{"id":359,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: unit coverage for store and adapter layers must prove no-leak behavior in persistence, replay caches, audit metadata, and evidence-handle generation, with logs that identify the exact rule and payload path under test.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:27Z"}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.9","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add unit tests for snapshot/status/digest/attention/inspect assembly and renderer projections","description":"Add focused package-local unit tests for the robot surfaces themselves so section assembly and renderer semantics stay stable. This task exists because user-facing breakage often happens where normalized state is turned into actual outputs, and that layer deserves direct verification in addition to goldens and E2E coverage.","design":"The tests should cover snapshot, status, digest, attention, inspect, and diagnostics assembly; section presence and omission rules; empty-array semantics; next_actions and remediation hints; request or outcome correlation handles; operator attention-state markers; inspect lookup behavior; invalid-target error handling; renderer omission signaling; truncation or pagination cues; aggregation or suppression cues; JSON, TOON, markdown, and terse projection rules; payload-budget markers where applicable; explanation handles and evidence summaries where the contract exposes them; and deterministic ordering. They should use the shared fixture corpus and log surface name, schema ID, scenario name, render format, changed sections, payload sizes, request or outcome IDs, operator-state markers, suppression markers, error codes, diagnostic handles, and field-level or textual diffs that explain failures clearly.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the robot surface assembly and renderer logic are pinned by unit tests that catch semantic drift early and produce rich debugging output when outputs change, including for safe retries, correlated outcomes, compact attention presentation, and durable operator control.","notes":"The point is to test semantics, not just serializer mechanics. Every assertion should make it easier to understand what user-visible behavior changed.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23